SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1141
By Crowe
A RESOLUTION to commend Alvin Cole III for exemplary service
as a legislative intern.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, this body is pleased to recognize certain persons
who have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the betterment of the legislative
process; and
WHEREAS, Alvin Cole III is one such individual, who has distinguished himself in his
role as a legislative intern for Senator Rusty Crowe; Mr. Cole's work has resulted in innumerable
benefits for the legislators he assisted and the General Assembly as a whole; and
WHEREAS, originally from Memphis, Alvin Cole is the son of Julia Allen and Alvin Cole,
Jr., and has two siblings; he has learned a lot from his parents and his late grandfather, Alvin
Cole, Sr.; and
WHEREAS, a senior at Tennessee State University (TSU), where he is highly regarded
by his peers, Alvin Cole has achieved academic success as a member of the Dean's List and
the President's List, while participating in numerous extracurricular activities, including serving
as vice president of the Phi Beta Sigma Fraternity, Inc., a resident assistant, a Student Court
Justice, a member of the Honors College, and parliamentarian of the Urban Studies Honor
Society; he also participated in the Tennessee Internship Mock Session and won the position of
Governor; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Cole is slated to graduate summa cum laude with honors and distinction
and a 3.8 grade point average this May, earning both a Bachelor of Science degree in Political
Science and a Bachelor of Science degree in Urban Studies with a concentration in pre-law;
upon graduating, he will attend TSU's Master of Public Administration program with plans to
later attend law school and become a civil rights and public service attorney; and
SJR1141
017923
- 1 -

WHEREAS, in addition to his outstanding academics, Alvin Cole has contributed greatly
to his community; he has participated in multiple urban mentorships and cleanup opportunities,
including clothing drives, Project Cure, and Letters to the Incarcerated; and
WHEREAS, a personal motto Mr. Cole lives by is, "Be who Jesus is to you, to others,
and always keep Him first"; and
WHEREAS, eager to familiarize himself with the characteristics and complexities of
Tennessee State government and to further his studies, Alvin Cole brought his many abilities
and singular expertise to Capitol Hill for the 2026 session of the One Hundred Fourteenth
General Assembly; and
WHEREAS, throughout the 2026 legislative session, Mr. Cole has surpassed all criteria
that define a devoted and conscientious legislative intern; and
WHEREAS, Alvin Cole has performed his many duties with extraordinary insight and
rare decorum; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend Alvin Cole III for outstanding
service as a legislative intern for Senator Rusty Crowe and extend to him our best wishes for
every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
